    "objective": "“To model and re-evaluate the pharmacokinetics of carbamazepine (CBZ) and CBZ-10, 11epoxide (CBZ-E) after 5 day b.i.d. dosing with either Carbatrol® (extended-release beads) or Tegretol-XR (an osmotic pump tablet, an Oros® tablet) using compartmental method.”",
    "covariates": "Michaelis menten (amount of drug in system as predictor of clearance) WT on volume for CBZ and CBZE, WT on Vmax",
    "observations": "Michaelis menten kinetics of CBZ and CBZE, allowing to predict the time to stabilisation of PK. Formula for time to plateau given, thereby allowing uptitration optimisation. Unclear how much variability was explained by covariates.",
    "dose": "Multiple oral doses in healthy subjects",
    "structure": "2 compartment linear absorption and elimination for CBZ and CBZE, plus michaelis menten conversion CBZ to CBZE",
    "equations": "lag time=theta1*(1+eta1) duration=theta2*(1+eta2) K10=theta3*(1+eta3) V2=theta4*WT*(1+eta4) Km=theta5*(1+eta5) Vmax=theta6*WT*(1+eta6) K30=theta7*(1+eta7) V3=theta8*WT*(1+eta8) n=theta9*(1+eta9) RATE=F*DOSE/duration dA1/dt=DOSE - RATE dA2/dt= RATE -(V2*Vmax*A2**n)/((V2*Km)**n+A2**n) –K20*A2 dA3/dt= (V2*Vmax*A2**n)/((V2*Km)**n+A2**n) –K30*A3 Compartment numbers were changed to make more physiological sense (absorption compartment was number 2 in original paper)",
    "parameter_values": "theta1=0.02 theta2=12.1 theta3=0.024 theta4=1.119 theta5=28.639 theta6=0.085 theta7=0.128 theta8=0.728 theta9=4.50 omega1=0.25 omega2=0.00027 omega3=0.06 omega4=0.0294 omega5=0.1024 omega6=0.31 omega7=0.13 omega8=0.0533 omega9=0.180",
